# TaskFlow: Architecture Documentation

This document describes the architectural design of the TaskFlow Enterprise-Grade Task Management System.

## 1. High-Level Overview

TaskFlow is a full-stack web application following a client-server architecture. The frontend is a Single Page Application (SPA), and the backend provides a RESTful API. Both are containerized using Docker and orchestrated with Docker Compose.

```mermaid
graph TD
    User[End User (Browser)] -- HTTP/HTTPS --> CDN(CDN / Load Balancer)
    CDN --> Nginx(Nginx Proxy / Static Server)
